.TH LPF-SUPPORT-BUNDLE 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-support\-bundle \- collect redacted diagnostic evidence
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf support\-bundle
.SH DESCRIPTION
Collect redacted diagnostic evidence for support and release validation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-output <path>
write the bundle to a target directory or archive
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf support\-bundle \-\-output /tmp/lpf\-support
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Never include raw secrets, private keys, packet payloads, or unredacted inventory.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-history(8), lpf\-man(8)
